In a speech, Vice President Kamala Harris expressed her commitment to safeguarding and strengthening the freedom to vote. She highlighted the importance of passing the Freedom to Vote Act and the John Lewis Voting Rights Advancement Act, as well as taking executive action. Harris also made several announcements, including the release of a report by the National Institute of Standards and Technology on the barriers faced by disabled Americans when voting and proposed actions to protect the voting rights of members of Tribal Nations and Native communities. Additionally, new guidance was announced to make it easier for federal employees to vote and serve as nonpartisan election workers. Harris commended the agencies present for their innovative work and emphasized the significance of voting rights for democracy and the country's standing in the world.